, would recite in the two Eid prayers and in the Friday prayer the chapters, \u201cGlorify the name of your Lord the Most High,\u201d (87:1) and, \u201cHas there come to you the news of the overwhelming?\u201d (88:1).\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19596,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/07\/26\/qaf-al-qamar-salat-eid\/","url_meta":{"origin":19612,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Eid: Surat Qaf and al-Qamar recited in Eid prayers","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 26, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Waqid reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, would recite in the Eid prayers, \"Qaf, by the majestic Quran,\" (50:1) and, \"The Hour approaches and the moon is cleft asunder,\" (54:1). Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 891 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim \u0639\u0646 \u0623\u0628\u064a \u0648\u064e\u0627\u0642\u0650\u062f\u064d \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u064a\u0652\u062b\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19589,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/07\/26\/seven-five-takbir-salat-eid\/","url_meta":{"origin":19612,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Eid: Seven and five Takbir in Eid prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 26, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"'Amr ibn 'Awf reported: The Prophet,